            <h1 style="text-align: center;">School Administrative Unit (SAU) 21 COVID-19 Information</h1>

<p style="text-align: center;">SAU 21 continues to actively monitor updates from the Center for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), the New Hampshire Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS), the New Hampshire Department of Education (NHDOE), and other SAUs in our region and throughout the state.  As always, our priorities include the safety of our students, clear communication with parents, guardians and community members, and maintaining a sense of normalcy for our staff and students.</p>

<p style="text-align: center;">Please find the most recent SAU 21 communication and information regarding the novel coronavirus COVID-19 by clicking the documents below:</p>

<h3 style="text-align: center;"><a href="/files/documents/Remote%20Learning%20Update%20(4.16.2020)%20(1).pdf"><u><strong>April 16th, 2020 Letter From The Superintendent</strong></u></a></h3>

